{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"55f5b695-edba-4893-81e7-6a2a5f3b17c5","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8, the VSTest flags map to new platform extensions. The equivalent command is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n`--filter` stays before `--`; platform-specific flags go after it.\n\n**Required NuGet packages:**\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\nAnd set `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` in your project/`Directory.Build.props`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f56e504c-4f34-4142-9cb3-c5278c506707","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling migration, not a codebase task. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`  (same, but uses `--treenode-filter` for the new filter syntax, though `--filter` is still supported for compatibility)\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage, or you configure it differently\n\n\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWhen using `dotnet test` with the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner enabled via the project file setting, the command-line arguments shift to match the platform's native syntax rather than VSTest's conventions.\n\nLooking at the specific argument mappings: filters work similarly or can use `--treenode-filter`, TRX logging becomes `--report-trx`, code coverage switches to `--collect-coverage`, and crash/hang diagnostics map to their respective dump flags. Each of these features requires installing the corresponding extension package. When running through `dotnet test`, arguments get passed through using a `--` separator to distinguish them from dotnet's own options.\n\nFor .NET 8 specifically with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I need to add the `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner` property to the project file to enable the new test runner.\n\nThe command structure uses `--filter` for `dotnet test` arguments, then passes platform-specific options like `--report-trx`, `--collect-coverage`, and dump settings after `--`. For code coverage in cobertura format, I'd need to specify `--coverage-output-format cobertura` or configure it through a `.runsettings` file.","outputTokens":1234,"requestId":"4816:BAEFE:3254E3A:36EA33E:69FBE339"},"id":"032a3f22-b697-4745-8533-40f06259422d","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:56:46.950Z","parentId":"d37043f3-ffb8-45a1-946c-55d51bfcfdac"}
